# Committed placeholder env for `prisma-composer dev` (spec §5, ADR-0041).
#
# `prisma-composer dev` runs the real deploy pipeline against local providers, so
# it validates every service input at converge time. The email module's
# deliveryMode/from and the auth module's baseUrl are operator `envParam`s — the
# dev harness auto-placeholders the SECRET slot but NOT env-sourced params
# (local-dev.md: a missing envParam is a hard error), so they must be present in
# the dev shell. The `dev` script sources this file, so the one command needs no
# hand-set variables. These are placeholders, not secrets: local delivery is
# `none`, and the junk credential is unused in `none` mode.
EMAIL_DELIVERY_MODE=none
EMAIL_FROM=auth@example.test
AUTH_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3000
EMAIL_DELIVERY_CREDENTIAL=none-mode-unused-credential
